        * Nittaku G-1: Higher ceiling when you swing hard; strong second-gear acceleration and finishing power. :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}
        * NUZN 45: Good top end, but tuned more for controllable power than pure maximum pace. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}
    * **Linearity:**
        * Nittaku G-1: More linear/direct; predictable power scaling when you add force. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}
        * NUZN 45: Slightly more “tensor bounce” feel; still designed to stay balanced and not overly jumpy. :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}

* **Spin Mechanics:**
    * **Opening Loop:**
        * Nittaku G-1: Excellent vs backspin if your brush is solid; high throw helps lift and clear the net. :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}
        * NUZN 45: Very user-friendly for first loop; slightly tacky topsheet helps grab and lift with less perfect contact. :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}
    * **Max Spin:**
