### 3. The Recommendation
* **Choose Nittaku G-1 if:**
    * You generate your own power and want a higher top-end with heavy, high-arc spin. :contentReference[oaicite:19]{index=19}
    * You value linearity and crisp feedback for full-stroke looping and counter-looping.
    * You want a proven, all-round offensive rubber that stays stable when rallies speed up.

* **Choose NUZN 45 if:**
    * You want easier access to spin and control at medium effort, especially on the opening loop. :contentReference[oaicite:20]{index=20}
    * You like a slightly tacky hybrid feel for safer short game and more “grab” on soft contacts. :contentReference[oaicite:21]{index=21}
    * You prioritize precision and consistency over maximum finishing speed.